I need you to find her.

16:36.299 --> 16:38.171
If she was treated here
after the attack,

16:38.214 --> 16:39.346
then she's in the system.

16:39.389 --> 16:41.652
Okay, well, he's got
the fMRI today.

16:41.696 --> 16:43.567
We'll find out
if he's in there.

16:43.611 --> 16:44.829
I'll prep him for the magnet.

16:44.873 --> 16:47.006
Oh, hey, Seth.

16:48.920 --> 16:51.184
I want the results sealed
to everyone but me, okay?

16:51.227 --> 16:52.663
Well, that's not protocol.

16:52.707 --> 16:54.970
That's not protocol?

16:55.014 --> 16:57.233
Does that look like protocol
lying in that fucking bed?

16:57.277 --> 16:59.279
[ Monitors beeping ]

17:03.065 --> 17:09.811
♪♪

17:09.854 --> 17:11.856
So, who was that girl?

17:11.900 --> 17:13.641
What does she mean to you?

17:13.684 --> 17:15.947
[ Beeping continues ]

17:15.991 --> 17:20.300
♪♪

17:20.343 --> 17:23.259
All right,
listen to me, Brady.

17:23.303 --> 17:26.958
We are both on the same side,
okay?

17:27.002 --> 17:29.439
I'm your "get out of vegetative
state free" card.

17:29.483 --> 17:31.833
Add to that,

17:31.876 --> 17:34.575
should you be brought up to
trial, I'm your defense.

17:34.618 --> 17:37.839
I've seen
your orbital cortex.

17:37.882 --> 17:41.060
I can point to
the low activity,

17:41.103 --> 17:43.105
the genetic variants.

17:43.149 --> 17:48.110
I will testify that you had
no control over your actions.

17:48.154 --> 17:50.591
Do you see what I'm saying,
Brady?

17:50.634 --> 17:52.897
I'm not just talking about
bringing you back to life

17:52.941 --> 17:54.725
but a free life at that.

17:54.769 --> 17:58.338
But to do that, you and I,
we need to work together.

18:00.949 --> 18:03.082
Come on.

18:03.125 --> 18:13.092
♪♪

18:13.135 --> 18:23.276
♪♪

18:23.319 --> 18:25.582
Hodges: Is this the only camera
you have?

18:25.626 --> 18:26.844
Montez:
Thought it was enough.

18:26.888 --> 18:28.846
He's got an odd kind of swagger,
doesn't he?

18:28.890 --> 18:30.196
Mm-hmm.

18:30.239 --> 18:32.067
Heavy work boots.

18:32.111 --> 18:33.416
Did you find any tread?

18:33.460 --> 18:35.244
Uh, right here.

18:35.288 --> 18:36.811
Uh, size 12 Timberland.

18:36.854 --> 18:39.466
They sold 2,300 of them in the
last 5 years in this county.

18:39.509 --> 18:41.381
Fuck.

18:41.424 --> 18:44.514
Okay, I've been through combat,
and I can't watch this shit.

18:45.776 --> 18:46.734
[ Mouse clicks ]

18:46.777 --> 18:48.866
Ah, Jesus.

18:48.910 --> 18:50.390
[ Laptop closes ]

18:50.433 --> 18:53.871
Problem is, you're not
telling me everything.

18:55.482 --> 18:57.701
You're not.

18:57.745 --> 19:00.008
So maybe this is a good time
to start, right?

19:02.271 --> 19:04.186
I don't know much.

19:04.230 --> 19:06.536
As for what you do know?

19:08.843 --> 19:12.325
Our Dr. Frankenstein
has done some experiments

19:12.368 --> 19:15.850
on regenerating the brain.

19:15.893 --> 19:18.157
He's had some positive
developments with our friend.

19:19.593 --> 19:21.682
That's why I was running
a little interference,

19:21.725 --> 19:24.075
tried to back you off.

19:24.119 --> 19:25.686
So what's your angle?

19:27.557 --> 19:29.559
Come on. You haven't exactly
been playing by the book,

19:29.603 --> 19:31.170
have ya?

19:31.213 --> 19:33.563
You got an angle?

19:33.607 --> 19:36.175
Maybe a little celebrity
of my own.

19:36.218 --> 19:38.307
And what do I get?

19:38.351 --> 19:39.961
Someone kills
my fucking dog.

19:40.004 --> 19:41.571
Yeah.

19:43.486 --> 19:44.835
Yeah.

19:44.879 --> 19:48.361
You know, I --
I believe in God.

19:48.404 --> 19:51.538
You know,
like heaven and shit.

19:51.581 --> 19:55.542
I figure when someone dies,
you can still connect with them.

19:55.585 --> 19:58.109
I still talk to my mother.
I know she can hear me.

19:58.153 --> 20:02.113
But with a dog...

20:02.157 --> 20:06.466
it's all about, like,
the eye contact and the touch.

20:09.643 --> 20:12.385
When a dog is gone,
I don't know,

20:12.428 --> 20:14.865
it's like the most gone
there is.

20:14.909 --> 20:16.867
Yeah, that's why
I got a tortoise.

20:16.911 --> 20:18.347
You know,
figures to outlive me,

20:18.391 --> 20:19.696
so I don't have to
concern myself

20:19.740 --> 20:22.395
with talking to him in heaven
or any of that.

20:22.438 --> 20:24.484
What do you mean,
like a turtle?

20:24.527 --> 20:27.226
I mean like a tortoise.

20:27.269 --> 20:30.272
I don't care for turtles.

20:32.666 --> 20:35.408
Who else was on the floor
when you were talking to Brady?

20:35.451 --> 20:36.974
I was the only one
in the room.

20:37.018 --> 20:38.498
I mean, yes, there were people
in the fucking corridor --

20:38.541 --> 20:40.413
doctors, nurses, and shit.

20:42.719 --> 20:44.982
Wait a minute.
There was, um...

20:45.026 --> 20:47.898
There was a big guy.

20:47.942 --> 20:52.773
He was, uh, pushing a --
a book cart or something,

20:52.816 --> 20:55.166
but he couldn't have fucking
heard what I said.

20:55.210 --> 20:57.734
I'm not going crazy. I was the
only one in the fucking room.

21:00.128 --> 21:03.305
Who'd be so depraved
to stab an innocent dog?

21:03.349 --> 21:05.481
Another reason
for the tortoise.

21:05.525 --> 21:07.396
Yeah, they got
the hard shell.

21:11.008 --> 21:14.795
All right, let me see if I can
check any of that stuff out.

21:14.838 --> 21:16.884
The doctor's name is Babineau.

21:16.927 --> 21:20.583
B-A-B-I-N-E-A-U.

21:20.627 --> 21:22.411
Just see what you can pull up.

21:22.455 --> 21:24.413
Okay. And can't you just
question him directly?

21:24.457 --> 21:25.806
I mean, see what he --

21:25.849 --> 21:27.416
No.
Doctor/patient privilege.

21:27.460 --> 21:30.071
Anyway,
from what I'm gathering,

21:30.114 --> 21:31.333
he doesn't figure
to be forthcoming.

21:31.377 --> 21:33.030
Just get on it, will ya?

21:33.074 --> 21:35.642
Okay. And where are you
heading now?

21:35.685 --> 21:37.426
I'm meeting an acquaintance
for coffee.

21:37.470 --> 21:38.732
An acquaintance?
What acquaintance?

21:38.775 --> 21:40.603
Like, a "none of my business"
acquaintance

21:40.647 --> 21:42.605
or a work-related
acquaintance?

21:42.649 --> 21:44.781
Jesus balls.
Are we married now?

21:44.825 --> 21:47.218
Oh, "Jesus balls" yourself.

21:47.262 --> 21:49.873
Your vulgarity doesn't work
on me anymore.

21:49.917 --> 21:53.355
Just get on Babineau,
would you, please?

21:53.399 --> 21:55.139
Technician:
Let's get him stabilized.

21:55.183 --> 21:56.793
All right.

21:56.837 --> 21:58.099
Okay, that's good.

21:58.142 --> 22:00.536
[ Indistinct talking ]

22:00.580 --> 22:02.930
You got enough tubing?

22:02.973 --> 22:03.844
Yeah, give me
a little bit more.

22:03.887 --> 22:06.020
Okay.

22:06.063 --> 22:08.544
[ Machine whirs ]

22:17.379 --> 22:18.859
[ Whirring stops ]

22:22.384 --> 22:24.517
[ Sighs ]

22:29.957 --> 22:33.395
[ Machine pulsating ]

22:35.136 --> 22:37.704
[ Rumbling ]

22:37.747 --> 22:40.054
[ Clattering ]

22:46.190 --> 22:49.759
Man: We're soaring over
the Empire State Building.

22:49.803 --> 22:53.937
At 102 stories high
and almost 1,500 feet tall,

22:53.981 --> 22:56.070
the art-deco building
was originally part...

22:56.113 --> 22:58.594
[ Rumbling intensifies ]

23:02.772 --> 23:05.166
John Jacob Astor's descendants
building the...

23:14.175 --> 23:16.395
[ Pulsating continues ]

23:33.716 --> 23:35.936
[ Dog barking in distance ]

23:40.506 --> 23:42.638
So, how you doing
overall?

23:44.379 --> 23:47.426
Uh...

23:47.469 --> 23:49.428
Pretty good.
Pretty good.

23:50.994 --> 23:53.606
[ Sighs ]

23:53.649 --> 23:55.477
Oh, yeah, I mean,
you said "overall,"

23:55.521 --> 24:00.264
so [chuckles] overall, I'm doing
really shitty, actually.

24:00.308 --> 24:02.441
How are you?

24:04.094 --> 24:06.009
Pretty much the same.

24:06.053 --> 24:08.621
Uh...

24:08.664 --> 24:13.843
The word is that
when you visited him,

24:13.887 --> 24:15.889
his heart rate shot up.

24:15.932 --> 24:17.717
[ Chuckles ]

24:17.760 --> 24:19.719
[ Clears throat ]
So -- so does that mean

24:19.762 --> 24:22.896
that he somehow knew
that I was there?

24:22.939 --> 24:24.941
I don't know.

24:24.985 --> 24:28.510
I mean,
to be honest with ya...

24:31.121 --> 24:32.688
...I'm -- I'm --
I'm finding it hard

24:32.732 --> 24:34.124
to keep up
with the science of it,

24:34.168 --> 24:37.954
but bottom line seems to be
that anything is possible.

24:39.869 --> 24:42.132
Fuck.

24:42.176 --> 24:44.526
Yeah, you and me both.

24:44.570 --> 24:48.661
I thought that I was gonna
feel better going to see him,

24:48.704 --> 24:53.187
that I'd get some sort of,
like...

24:53.230 --> 24:55.885
closure
or some sort of shit,

24:55.929 --> 24:58.279
and I didn't.

24:58.322 --> 25:01.151
I just feel fucking worse.

25:01.195 --> 25:03.023
[ Sighs ]
You know the worst part?

25:03.066 --> 25:06.809
The worst part is that
I kind of felt bad for him

25:06.853 --> 25:12.032
lying there with
all that shit in the bed.

25:12.075 --> 25:15.470
I felt bad for him,
for Brady Hartsfield.

25:15.514 --> 25:18.691
I don't want to fucking feel bad
for Brady Hartsfield.

25:18.734 --> 25:20.997
Did you say anything
to him?

25:21.041 --> 25:23.913
A couple -- couple things.

25:23.957 --> 25:26.655
Uh, he stabbed me,
so I kind of had a bone to pick.

25:26.699 --> 25:28.396
[ Laughs ]

25:28.439 --> 25:30.833
[ Chuckles ]
Good for you.

25:36.099 --> 25:37.884
I...

25:39.668 --> 25:44.368
I feel bad...

25:44.412 --> 25:46.414
for everything that's happened
to you.

25:46.457 --> 25:49.112
You tried to warn me.

25:49.156 --> 25:50.723
Remember?

25:52.072 --> 25:55.379
Told you you had
the wrong ice-cream man.

25:58.078 --> 26:01.951
I feel like, um, when I was
standing in that room,

26:01.995 --> 26:05.346
that he was still among us.

26:05.389 --> 26:07.827
I don't know
if you've felt that.

26:09.959 --> 26:12.222
I don't think he's gone.

26:14.224 --> 26:16.139
You know what they say,

26:16.183 --> 26:20.187
that nobody's really gone,
right, even after they die?

26:20.230 --> 26:24.495
That, like, they live on

26:24.539 --> 26:26.976
in the people that
they leave behind.

26:28.848 --> 26:33.722
And for Brady Hartsfield,
that's, uh -- that's you and me.

26:33.766 --> 26:36.116
That's about it.

26:43.253 --> 26:45.647
[ Keyboard clacking ]

26:45.691 --> 26:47.649
Technician: All right,
when I played the description

26:47.693 --> 26:49.869
of the Empire State Building
for him, uh,

26:49.912 --> 26:53.133
increased blood flowed to
the parahippocampal gyrus.

26:53.176 --> 26:54.613
Then I played the commercial
about

26:54.656 --> 26:55.875
Taylor Swift's
facial structure,

26:55.918 --> 26:58.442
and it triggered
the fusiform gyrus region

26:58.486 --> 27:00.619
just like a healthy,
conscious patient.

27:00.662 --> 27:03.622
I mean, he's in there.
It's pretty clear.

27:17.157 --> 27:18.898
Al? Al Jursak?

27:18.941 --> 27:21.814
That's my name.
What can I do ya for?

27:21.857 --> 27:23.859
I'm Bill Hodges.
I'm a private investigator.

27:23.903 --> 27:26.340
P.I.?
You mean like Magnum?

27:26.383 --> 27:28.124
No, sir.

27:28.168 --> 27:30.605
No, no. Baretta, huh?
Nor him.

27:30.649 --> 27:32.607
Uh, may I ask you
a few questions if
you've got a minute?

27:32.651 --> 27:35.392
Well, I-I-I kind of do
have to get home soon,

27:35.436 --> 27:38.482
uh, 'cause I-I promised Reggie
I'd give him a haircut.

27:38.526 --> 27:39.875
Ah, yeah?
Who -- who's Reggie?

27:39.919 --> 27:41.224
He's my brother.

27:41.268 --> 27:44.314
See, I give him haircuts,
he makes me soup.

27:44.358 --> 27:46.447
Ah, that sounds like
a good plan.

27:46.490 --> 27:48.797
Do you remember
a Mr. Montez?

27:48.841 --> 27:50.799
The district attorney man.Yeah, yeah.

27:50.843 --> 27:52.888
Remember the first time that
he visited Brady Hartsfield?

27:52.932 --> 27:55.456
Were you in the room?No. Oh, no, no, no, sir.

27:55.499 --> 27:58.067
Dr. Babineau told everyone

27:58.111 --> 28:01.897
to give him and Mr. Montez
total privacy.

28:01.941 --> 28:04.944
Okay, all right, well, listen,
do you mind me asking you,

28:04.987 --> 28:06.815
where were you
yesterday afternoon?

28:10.166 --> 28:12.473
I-I-I-I don't remember.

28:12.516 --> 28:14.649
You don't remember?
No, sir.

28:14.693 --> 28:17.391
That happen to you often,
that you don't remember where
you were yesterday afternoon?

28:17.434 --> 28:20.481
Well, uh, I don't know.
[ Stammers ]

28:20.524 --> 28:21.830
Most -- most of the times,
I do,

28:21.874 --> 28:24.311
but sometimes I don't.
[ Chuckles ]

28:24.354 --> 28:28.707
Well, if you remember,
will you remember to call me?

28:30.143 --> 28:32.362
[ Chuckles ] Yes, mister.

28:32.406 --> 28:34.060
Yeah, sure.
I will, sir.

28:34.103 --> 28:36.976
What you got going on your door
there?

28:37.019 --> 28:39.108
Oh! Oh, that's just
probably blood.

28:39.152 --> 28:42.111
Blood?Yeah, you know, we get it
in our shoes in the E.R.

28:42.155 --> 28:45.811
You know,
blood, urine, feces.

28:45.854 --> 28:47.290
You don't wear booties?

28:47.334 --> 28:51.077
Oh, no, we absolutely do,
but sometimes they tear.

28:51.120 --> 28:55.516
You know, uh, actually, uh,
a lot of times, they tear.

28:55.559 --> 28:57.736
Here, let me clean it off
for ya.

28:57.779 --> 28:58.867
Oh, no, no,
you don't have to do that.

28:58.911 --> 29:00.347
No, no, no.That's okay. No, but it's --

29:00.390 --> 29:02.044
It's okay.
You okay with that?

29:02.088 --> 29:05.091
You okay if I clean the blood
off your car there, Mr. Jursak?

29:05.134 --> 29:06.919
Of course, of course.

29:06.962 --> 29:11.488
[ Chuckles ] You know, mister,
you really are a nice man.

29:13.186 --> 29:14.927
Yeah, you have yourself
a good afternoon.

29:14.970 --> 29:16.363
You, too, sir.

29:16.406 --> 29:18.147
And -- and -- and -- and
thanks again for, you know...

29:25.198 --> 29:26.242
[ Car door closes ]

29:26.286 --> 29:28.505
[ Engine starts ]

29:39.995 --> 29:42.781
This is -- this is fantastic,
Felix.

29:42.824 --> 29:44.086
Yeah.

29:44.130 --> 29:45.871
He communicated.

29:45.914 --> 29:48.221
He communicated.

29:48.264 --> 29:49.875
I mean, as far as
"fuck offs" go,

29:49.918 --> 29:52.703
this one can be monetized
for a billion dollars

29:52.747 --> 29:54.793
and who knows
how many multiples.

29:54.836 --> 29:56.577
Yeah.

29:58.579 --> 30:00.929
Why the ambivalence?

30:00.973 --> 30:02.452
[ Sighs ]

30:02.496 --> 30:04.063
Honestly?

30:04.106 --> 30:05.847
[ Chuckles ]

30:05.891 --> 30:08.545
Kind of scared me
a little bit.

30:08.589 --> 30:11.940
And, you know, first on a,
"What have I done?" level.

30:11.984 --> 30:14.464
And second?

30:14.508 --> 30:17.859
[ Sighs ] Well, he's --
he's a killer.

30:17.903 --> 30:20.296
He's murdered people.

30:20.340 --> 30:22.777
I was suddenly
afraid of him.

30:22.821 --> 30:25.040
Well, what do you think
he's gonna do?

30:25.084 --> 30:27.216
He's just gonna hop out of
the bed and come after you?

30:27.260 --> 30:28.957
No.

30:30.916 --> 30:33.048
All I can say is
I was frightened.

30:34.528 --> 30:36.791
Do you know what the most
terrifying thing
in the world is?

30:41.143 --> 30:42.579
Success.

30:44.190 --> 30:47.541
So maybe you and I should
both be scared shitless.

30:48.847 --> 30:50.413
[ Sighs ]

30:50.457 --> 30:54.156
Felix, we did it.

30:54.200 --> 30:57.507
You -- you did it.

30:57.551 --> 31:01.729
Do you realize how close you are
to becoming a household name?

31:01.772 --> 31:03.513
And not just in
the medical industry.

31:03.557 --> 31:04.993
This is huge.

31:05.037 --> 31:07.256
Maybe. [ Chuckles ]

31:07.300 --> 31:11.391
I am so...proud of you.

31:11.434 --> 31:12.958
[ Chuckles ]

31:17.527 --> 31:19.529
[ Both chuckle ]What are you doing?

31:19.573 --> 31:21.183
Oh, you don't -- you don't know
what I'm doing?

31:21.227 --> 31:22.750
Hmm?

31:22.793 --> 31:24.621
Why don't we go upstairs?

31:24.665 --> 31:26.362
Why?
We don't have kids yet.

31:26.406 --> 31:29.452
What have you got
against kitchens, huh?

31:35.676 --> 31:39.071
Cornell undergrad,
Columbia Medical,

31:39.114 --> 31:41.421
and he did his residency at
New York-Presbyterian Hospital.

31:41.464 --> 31:43.292
Mr. All America
right here.

31:43.336 --> 31:46.078
Mm, his wife, Cora,
works for Vitalta.

31:46.121 --> 31:47.775
A pharma company?

31:47.818 --> 31:49.603
Yeah.

31:49.646 --> 31:51.866
Uh, made its name
with ErythoFlo.

31:51.910 --> 31:53.433
It's a stroke drug.

31:53.476 --> 31:54.913
ErythoFlo.
Mm-hmm.

31:54.956 --> 31:56.697
ErythoFlo.

31:56.740 --> 31:58.786
Hmm.
It says it's 98% similar

31:58.829 --> 32:02.572
to a drug created by
a Jiànkang Ni Pharmatech.

32:02.616 --> 32:04.270
Jiànkang.Does that help us at all?

32:04.313 --> 32:05.967
Let's see.

32:06.011 --> 32:10.711
Well, here's a photo of Cora
with the CEO of Jiànkang Ni.

32:10.754 --> 32:12.408
Mm.
This photo was taken

32:12.452 --> 32:15.063
one year before ErythoFlo
hit the market.

32:15.107 --> 32:17.022
That's interesting.

32:17.065 --> 32:18.980
Okay, look,
check this out.

32:19.024 --> 32:21.722
Amnesty International does not
like Cora Babineau's friends

32:21.765 --> 32:23.811
over here at Jiànkang.

32:23.854 --> 32:25.508
Let me see.

32:25.552 --> 32:28.120
It says they filed a lawsuit
alleging civil-rights violations

32:28.163 --> 32:30.687
in prisons.

32:30.731 --> 32:33.255
Look, gag orders all around
a month later.

32:33.299 --> 32:34.996
Okay, but what is
a pharmaceutical company

32:35.040 --> 32:37.085
doing in prisons?

32:39.174 --> 32:41.698
[ Insects chirping ]

32:53.580 --> 32:56.496
Give any more thought
to my suggestion

32:56.539 --> 32:59.716
about getting
some psychological help?

32:59.760 --> 33:02.241
Why do I need a shrink
when I got you, Ida?

33:02.284 --> 33:08.943
Well, if that's an invitation
for my analysis...

33:08.987 --> 33:12.381
you are an addict,

33:12.425 --> 33:15.080
and Brady is your drug.

33:17.038 --> 33:19.475
That it?
That all you got?

33:19.519 --> 33:23.305
He brought an intensity
to your life,

33:23.349 --> 33:25.699
an adrenaline high,
a dopamine rush --

33:25.742 --> 33:27.135
call it what you want.

33:27.179 --> 33:29.007
You became more alive

33:29.050 --> 33:31.270
when Brady Hartsfield
entered your life.

33:32.836 --> 33:37.102
He even unwittingly opened
you up to love with Janey.

33:37.145 --> 33:39.365
It certainly wasn't
his intention,

33:39.408 --> 33:45.197
but he made your life richer,
more exciting, more thrilling.

33:48.591 --> 33:50.767
He brought you back
from the dead, Bill.

33:50.811 --> 33:53.031
[ Dog barking in distance ]

33:53.074 --> 33:57.905
Which...might explain why

33:57.948 --> 34:02.431
you're trying to bring himback
from the dead.

34:05.260 --> 34:07.436
That's very impressive,
Ida.

34:07.480 --> 34:09.960
Here's the thing.

34:10.004 --> 34:13.573
It's not my imagination
that's bringing him back.

34:13.616 --> 34:16.793
He communicated with a doctor
today.

34:16.837 --> 34:19.144
[ Dog barks ]

34:19.187 --> 34:21.189
Really?

34:21.233 --> 34:24.062
That's the rumor.

34:24.105 --> 34:26.847
So the official line to anyone
who tells me I'm mad

34:26.890 --> 34:29.154
is that I'm gonna
ride the madness out

34:29.197 --> 34:30.633
just a little bit longer

34:30.677 --> 34:33.332
before I start flirting with
ways to get rid of it.

34:33.375 --> 34:35.029
My God.

34:35.073 --> 34:36.683
Yeah, I know.

34:38.119 --> 34:42.297
Bill, I found something
on the doctor and his wife.

34:42.341 --> 34:44.169
They're mixed up
in something.What?

34:44.212 --> 34:46.345
Well,
before we get into that,

34:46.388 --> 34:47.868
the preliminary results
came back

34:47.911 --> 34:50.044
from the blood
on Library Al's car.

34:50.088 --> 34:51.350
It's canine.

34:54.179 --> 34:55.876
[ Chuckles ]Yeah.

34:55.919 --> 34:58.139
[ Chuckles ] Cheers.

34:58.183 --> 35:00.576
[ Dog barks ]

35:01.882 --> 35:03.536
Do me a favor.

35:03.579 --> 35:05.407
If I go to break
this guy's fucking neck,

35:05.451 --> 35:07.235
just look the other way.

35:07.279 --> 35:09.194
We'll have none of that.

35:09.237 --> 35:10.978
We could be dealing with
diminished capacity.

35:11.021 --> 35:12.545
I really do think this guy's
a bit of a simpleton.

35:12.588 --> 35:14.590
A simple man
doesn't stab a dog.

35:14.634 --> 35:16.462
There's nothing simple
about this case.

35:16.505 --> 35:19.204
He killed my fucking dog.

35:19.247 --> 35:26.211
♪♪

35:26.254 --> 35:28.604
Seems to be the refrain.

35:28.648 --> 35:38.310
♪♪

35:38.353 --> 35:46.187
♪♪

35:46.231 --> 35:47.754
Motherfucker.

35:47.797 --> 35:49.538
Easy.

35:49.582 --> 35:59.200
♪♪

35:59.244 --> 36:00.506
Police!
Police!

36:00.549 --> 36:02.377
Hands where we can see them.Reggie! Reggie!

36:02.421 --> 36:03.770
Reggie!
[ Grunts ]

36:03.813 --> 36:06.729
[ Indistinct shouting ]

36:06.773 --> 36:08.514
Al! Al!

36:08.557 --> 36:09.993
Hey, Al!

36:10.037 --> 36:12.300
You motherfucker!
You killed my fucking dog!

36:12.344 --> 36:14.389
Fuck you, you piece of shit!

36:14.433 --> 36:15.869
I -- I didn't
do anything!

36:15.912 --> 36:18.088
Fuck you!Get your hands off
my fucking brother!

36:18.132 --> 36:20.134
Library Al:
I swear I didn't do anything!

36:20.178 --> 36:22.092
Hey, check it out.

36:22.136 --> 36:23.790
[ Cries ]

36:23.833 --> 36:26.836
Oh, no, no.
I didn't do anything.

36:26.880 --> 36:36.672
♪♪

36:36.716 --> 36:46.552
♪♪

36:48.641 --> 36:52.427
So they found the bloody gloves
and the knife,

36:52.471 --> 36:55.256
so he must be guilty.

36:55.300 --> 36:57.998
You would think so.

36:58.041 --> 36:59.608
But you don't think.

37:01.001 --> 37:03.221
You know when
you can smell evil?

37:03.264 --> 37:05.397
Well, you can sniff
the lack of it sometimes.

37:05.440 --> 37:09.009
I mean, no motive,
no record.

37:09.052 --> 37:11.925
Makes as much sense as Sadie
McDonald diving off that roof.

37:11.968 --> 37:15.363
And one thing that Sadie and
Library Al had in common...

37:15.407 --> 37:17.887
Brady Hartsfield.
Mm-hmm.

37:19.976 --> 37:23.719
Okay, so, this is everything I
have on the doctor and his wife.

37:23.763 --> 37:28.681
She has some serious ties to
this pharma company in China

37:28.724 --> 37:30.117
that just so happens
to be working on

37:30.160 --> 37:32.380
this big, uh, brain
regeneration drug.

37:32.424 --> 37:34.600
Wow.
Yeah.

37:34.643 --> 37:37.167
Just -- Just park that
for a second.

37:37.211 --> 37:38.778
Just take a seat,
Jerome, will ya?

37:41.824 --> 37:43.217
[ Sighs ]

37:43.261 --> 37:45.045
What are you doing here?

37:45.088 --> 37:48.570
Uh, tech support?

37:48.614 --> 37:51.051
Thought any more
about school?

37:51.094 --> 37:53.053
I'm on break.

37:53.096 --> 37:54.446
You going back?

37:54.489 --> 37:56.317
I don't know.

37:56.361 --> 37:58.363
I kind of like it here.

37:58.406 --> 38:00.321
Yeah,
that was my concern.

38:00.365 --> 38:02.541
[ Sighs ] Well, what's not
to like about this place?

38:02.584 --> 38:04.107
I mean...

38:04.151 --> 38:07.023
This is our lives.
It's your summer fling.

38:07.067 --> 38:08.547
What if I want this life?

38:08.590 --> 38:10.288
Who'd want this life?

38:10.331 --> 38:11.463
Hey.

38:11.506 --> 38:12.899
Me.

38:15.162 --> 38:16.598
Why?

38:16.642 --> 38:18.165
[ Sighs ]

38:20.559 --> 38:23.823
Because there's a world
that nobody talks about,

38:23.866 --> 38:25.738
a world that lives
under the surface

38:25.781 --> 38:28.567
of what we say is the world,
you know?

38:28.610 --> 38:30.220
The fuck you talking about?

38:30.264 --> 38:36.357
This world, i-it's the blood,
the oxygen, the air, you know,

38:36.401 --> 38:38.359
the lower G.I. system,
the things we can't see,

38:38.403 --> 38:40.535
but it's actually
really keeping us alive.

38:42.842 --> 38:44.539
Go on.

38:47.542 --> 38:50.589
I want to be
part of that world.

38:52.025 --> 38:54.375
That's fine.

38:54.419 --> 38:56.377
Be a part of it
with a Harvard degree.

38:58.205 --> 39:04.211
Harvard's lies and --
and whole subtext language,

39:04.254 --> 39:06.779
that's the complete opposite of
what's leaving people's mouths.

39:06.822 --> 39:08.563
You know that, right?

39:08.607 --> 39:10.522
It's actually
fucking designer labels

39:10.565 --> 39:12.262
and $100,000 cars

39:12.306 --> 39:15.178
and people calling me "bro"
and "homey" and "yo"

39:15.222 --> 39:16.832
just 'cause they swear
that they're cool

39:16.876 --> 39:19.444
or they're on some sort of
hipster-friendly wave

39:19.487 --> 39:23.491
or -- or this whole
post-modern meta-pseudo

39:23.535 --> 39:27.843
"I'm not really racist but
I'm actually fucking racist."

39:27.887 --> 39:30.803
It's fucking...

39:30.846 --> 39:34.415
It sucks.
It really sucks.

39:35.851 --> 39:37.984
You lost me at subtext.

39:42.989 --> 39:47.907
It's just cold and empty.

39:59.005 --> 40:00.833
This doesn't solve things.

40:02.269 --> 40:04.402
This would do it for now.

40:07.230 --> 40:09.972
And maybe you're right, Bill.

40:10.016 --> 40:12.366
'Cause I don't know anything.

40:15.369 --> 40:17.415
I don't know shit.

40:17.458 --> 40:19.417
No.

40:19.460 --> 40:21.462
Read those.

40:21.506 --> 40:22.507
Okay.

40:34.910 --> 40:36.999
Hodges: There is nothing here
for him.

40:37.043 --> 40:40.481
He's got an opportunity
that very few people get.

40:40.525 --> 40:42.788
If there's one thing I learned
from my mother,

40:42.831 --> 40:44.616
the hardest thing
about parenting

40:44.659 --> 40:47.053
is knowing when not to.

40:47.096 --> 40:48.707
The fuck does that mean?

40:48.750 --> 40:50.317
Hey, hey.

40:56.192 --> 40:58.412
[ Monitors beeping ]

41:01.850 --> 41:05.071
So, here's our golden boy.

41:16.169 --> 41:18.127
This isn't
Vitalta equipment.

41:18.171 --> 41:19.477
It's ours.

41:19.520 --> 41:21.827
It prevents muscle atrophy.

41:23.568 --> 41:25.352
Any more communication?

41:25.395 --> 41:27.223
No, nothing
since "fuck off."

41:30.357 --> 41:32.359
Hey, Brady.

41:34.056 --> 41:36.189
How you doing in there,
big guy?

41:36.232 --> 41:39.061
I'm Cora.

41:39.105 --> 41:41.411
I'm very much looking forward
to meeting you.

41:42.891 --> 41:44.763
Ooh.

41:44.806 --> 41:48.070
Wow, you're kind of cute.

41:48.114 --> 41:52.814
Doc, babe...

41:52.858 --> 41:55.600
you did not tell me
about wifey.

41:55.643 --> 41:58.603
Holy shit.

41:58.646 --> 42:01.344
What can I do to get you
to come out of that coma, huh?

42:01.388 --> 42:04.434
[ Beeping continues ]

42:04.478 --> 42:11.920
♪♪

42:11.964 --> 42:14.053
[ Monitors beeping rapidly ]

42:14.096 --> 42:16.882
Hey, wait,
his heart rate's going.

42:16.925 --> 42:18.840
I do have that effect
on people.

42:18.884 --> 42:25.891
♪♪

42:25.934 --> 42:28.589
[ Indistinct conversations ]

42:28.633 --> 42:30.591
Excuse me, Dr. Babineau?

42:30.635 --> 42:33.899
My name's Bill Hodges.
Might ring a bell or not.

42:33.942 --> 42:35.944
Uh, first of all,
let me congratulate you

42:35.988 --> 42:38.991
on your fine work,
both of you.

42:39.034 --> 42:41.602
You've made remarkable progress
with Mr. Hartsfield.

42:41.646 --> 42:44.300
I'm sorry.
I don't know what you mean.

42:44.344 --> 42:46.694
He's in a coma,
one that's likely irreversible.

42:46.738 --> 42:50.437
You know, modesty, I admire.
False modesty, not so much.

42:50.480 --> 42:53.614
Word is all over the hospital
and a bit beyond its walls,

42:53.658 --> 42:57.313
as well, that Brady
has an ability to communicate.

42:57.357 --> 43:00.273
Who told you
he communicated?

43:00.316 --> 43:02.362
I have several sources.

43:02.405 --> 43:03.406
I'm gonna get
right to the point.

43:03.450 --> 43:05.670
That would be nice.

43:05.713 --> 43:09.761
I've done my research
on you and you.

43:09.804 --> 43:13.547
You may have done some on me.
It's irrelevant.

43:13.591 --> 43:16.071
I have a special relationship
with Brady Hartsfield.

43:16.115 --> 43:18.813
You said that you were
getting to the point?

43:18.857 --> 43:20.162
I did.

43:20.206 --> 43:22.295
I can understand
your impatience.

43:22.338 --> 43:23.688
Time is money, right?

43:23.731 --> 43:26.125
And you've got a lot riding
on Brady's recovery,

43:26.168 --> 43:28.910
you and your Chinese
pharmaceutical affiliates.

43:28.954 --> 43:31.478
Okay, so, here's where
I can be of help.

43:31.521 --> 43:35.003
Now, you want Brady
to emerge, all right?

43:35.047 --> 43:37.223
It's possible,
in fact probable,

43:37.266 --> 43:39.312
that the only person
who can really get to him

43:39.355 --> 43:41.619
is the one
who already got to him.

43:41.662 --> 43:43.751
That would be me.

43:43.795 --> 43:45.797
So I'm offering --

43:45.840 --> 43:49.888
Let me be part of whatever
protocols you've got going here.

43:49.931 --> 43:53.369
I can get that crazy bastard
to crawl out of his hole.

43:53.413 --> 43:55.110
How exactly do you --

43:55.154 --> 43:56.938
We appreciate your offer,

43:56.982 --> 44:00.681
but there are no protocols at
play here out of the ordinary.

44:00.725 --> 44:04.511
And as far as my private
corporate interests,

44:04.554 --> 44:06.078
none of them have any bearing
on Brady Hartsfield

44:06.121 --> 44:07.949
or his treatment.

44:07.993 --> 44:09.995
So it's just a funny
coincidence, then,

44:10.038 --> 44:13.955
that your company makes
a brain-regenerating drug

44:13.999 --> 44:15.696
that could make you
billions of dollars

44:15.740 --> 44:17.611
should it prove
to be effective.

44:17.655 --> 44:19.221
Yeah, it certainly is
a coincidence.

44:19.265 --> 44:20.788
I mean, funny or not,

44:20.832 --> 44:23.095
I guess that does depend
on one's sense of humor.

44:23.138 --> 44:26.185
It's fucking funny.

44:26.228 --> 44:28.491
Now, let me be perfectly honest,
okay?

44:28.535 --> 44:31.364
I know what you're doing.
I know what you're up to.

44:31.407 --> 44:34.019
If you wake
this particular brain,

44:34.062 --> 44:38.153
you'll be opening a box that
you may not be able to close

44:38.197 --> 44:43.550
and shit so ugly you cannot
even imagine it will spill out.

44:45.247 --> 44:49.643
So let me be there
if it happens, okay?

44:49.687 --> 44:51.645
I'll even provoke the fucker.

44:53.603 --> 44:56.694
That way, if he does show up,

44:56.737 --> 44:59.566
I can put the cuffs on him
and we bring him to trial.

45:01.786 --> 45:04.310
And -- And if he doesn't
come out of hiding?

45:04.353 --> 45:06.268
We ship him
to a secure facility.

45:06.312 --> 45:08.706
No.
Never happen.

45:11.186 --> 45:12.884
Are you serious?

45:12.927 --> 45:14.407
100%, never happen.

45:17.018 --> 45:19.281
You're risking lives?

45:19.325 --> 45:21.501
[ Scoffs ]

45:21.544 --> 45:24.373
I think you're being a little
dramatic and a tad unhinged.

45:24.417 --> 45:29.596
Were we looking for help,
we would truly appreciate yours.

45:29.639 --> 45:31.380
Mm-hmm.

45:31.424 --> 45:34.253
You know, that sad fuck
is your lottery ticket

45:34.296 --> 45:36.603
only if he wakes up.

45:36.646 --> 45:40.085
The best bet to provoke him...

45:40.128 --> 45:42.087
right here.

45:42.130 --> 45:45.046
What's in it for you?

45:46.831 --> 45:49.050
He killed people dear to me,

45:49.094 --> 45:52.575
and given what's been going on
in your hospital lately,

45:52.619 --> 45:54.926
I'm not sure that his potential
has been capped.

45:54.969 --> 45:56.536
I'll take him dead,
I'll take him alive,

45:56.579 --> 45:59.147
I'll take him shipped out
outside the city

45:59.191 --> 46:01.584
where he cannot hurt people.

46:01.628 --> 46:03.543
But this in between shit...

46:07.503 --> 46:09.418
...it makes me nervous.

46:10.855 --> 46:13.292
Yeah, I really do
understand that.

46:13.335 --> 46:15.773
I wish that we
could help you.

46:18.297 --> 46:20.386
You need to wish harder.

46:35.880 --> 46:39.405
We need to move faster.
You need to wake him up.

46:39.448 --> 46:41.842
Come on, because some private
detective came and told --

46:41.886 --> 46:44.627
He's working for somebody,
Felix.

46:44.671 --> 46:46.673
My bet's the police.

46:46.716 --> 46:49.241
M-Maybe FBI,
I don't know.
What? Why?

46:49.284 --> 46:52.157
What, you think that he's coming
to us because he wants justice?

46:52.200 --> 46:54.333
Please. Who does that?

46:54.376 --> 46:57.031
That fat smurf
is on somebody's payroll,

46:57.075 --> 46:58.424
and it's either government
surveillance, or worse,

46:58.467 --> 47:00.426
it could be corporate.

47:00.469 --> 47:02.558
You need to
wake Hartsfield up

47:02.602 --> 47:05.866
before this all blows up in our
faces and it all gets shut down.

47:05.910 --> 47:08.303
They have no grounds
to shut us down.

47:08.347 --> 47:10.175
If anything, we're on
stronger turf than ever.

47:10.218 --> 47:12.133
He's snooping around in
our Chinese protocols,

47:12.177 --> 47:14.483
and it's making me
fucking nervous.

47:16.050 --> 47:17.356
Why?

47:19.488 --> 47:20.707
Cora, why?

47:27.061 --> 47:28.062
[ Engine shuts off ]

47:28.106 --> 47:30.108
[ Sighs ]

47:34.677 --> 47:36.679
So, you know that they
tested it on monkeys.

47:36.723 --> 47:38.377
Yeah.

47:39.987 --> 47:42.120
They didn't stop there.

47:42.163 --> 47:43.948
What are you saying?

47:43.991 --> 47:47.212
In a prison in China, they gave
a test group Cerebellin

47:47.255 --> 47:49.475
and they gave a control group
sugar pills,

47:49.518 --> 47:52.086
and the test group complained
of blinding headaches,

47:52.130 --> 47:55.524
persistent nausea,
exhibited signs of palsy.

47:55.568 --> 47:57.918
But it's what happened
to the control group

47:57.962 --> 48:00.007
that ended the experiment.

48:00.051 --> 48:02.009
Jesus, what happened?

48:02.053 --> 48:04.403
They all committed suicide.

48:04.446 --> 48:06.231
The test group?

48:06.274 --> 48:07.972
The control group.

48:08.015 --> 48:09.799
The one on the sugar pills.

48:09.843 --> 48:10.931
Why would sugar cause --

48:10.975 --> 48:12.628
It wasn't the sugar.

48:12.672 --> 48:14.892
The test group
got into their minds

48:14.935 --> 48:17.068
and fucked around in there.

48:17.111 --> 48:19.940
You're telling me
the test group

48:19.984 --> 48:22.377
caused the control group
to take their own lives?

48:26.033 --> 48:28.166
It's possible.

48:28.209 --> 48:30.603
It's very possible.

48:30.646 --> 48:32.170
And you didn't think
to tell me this before?

48:32.213 --> 48:34.085
I'm under strict
confidentiality.

48:34.128 --> 48:36.043
I'm your fucking husband!

48:36.087 --> 48:37.566
They're my employer.

48:39.090 --> 48:40.787
[ Scoffs ]

48:40.830 --> 48:42.789
Fuck.

48:42.832 --> 48:44.443
Felix.

48:48.012 --> 48:50.101
Fuck me.

48:50.144 --> 48:51.754
[ Car beeps ]

48:53.147 --> 48:55.019
Hey.

48:59.023 --> 49:01.808
Do not turn this into something
it's not.

49:01.851 --> 49:03.941
What the fuck am I
turning this into, Cora?

49:03.984 --> 49:05.899
I just need you
to stay focused.

49:05.943 --> 49:07.901
It's not hard to connect you
to Jiànkang Ni.

49:07.945 --> 49:10.034
No one's gonna care about that,
no one's gonna give two shits

49:10.077 --> 49:13.646
if you get in there and you open
him up and you get him talking.

49:13.689 --> 49:14.995
You.

49:15.039 --> 49:17.345
You put your forceps
on his regrown tissue

49:17.389 --> 49:19.043
and you tell him that
if he doesn't speak,

49:19.086 --> 49:20.827
you're gonna rip it out
of his fucking head.

49:20.870 --> 49:23.395
How am I supposed to justify
a craniotomy at this point?

49:23.438 --> 49:24.831
I don't know.
You had no choice

49:24.874 --> 49:26.441
due to increased
inter-cranial pressure.

49:26.485 --> 49:27.877
And what if they don't buy it?
What then?

49:27.921 --> 49:30.576
I do not function well
from a state of fear, Felix.

49:30.619 --> 49:31.751
Neither do I!

49:31.794 --> 49:34.710
Are you
fucking kidding me?

49:34.754 --> 49:36.408
[ Crying ] You don't get it,
you don't understand,

49:36.451 --> 49:39.802
and you can't understand,
because you were born safe.

49:39.846 --> 49:43.067
Oh, come on.
Don't give me that shit.

49:43.110 --> 49:44.851
You lied to me.

49:47.027 --> 49:49.943
If he remains in a coma, Felix,
and they get a warrant,

49:49.987 --> 49:51.727
we're never gonna
survive this.

49:51.771 --> 49:54.469
We will neversurvive.

50:01.694 --> 50:04.697
That -- That detective
may be nothing more

50:04.740 --> 50:06.351
than what he represented himself
to be.

50:08.005 --> 50:10.659
I know a man on a mission
when I see one,

50:10.703 --> 50:14.620
and I do not want to be
that man's mission.

50:14.663 --> 50:16.361
[ Crows cawing ]

50:18.841 --> 50:21.018
Fuck.

50:22.671 --> 50:25.544
How's it going, buddy?Whoa. No visitors.

50:25.587 --> 50:28.025
And I'm under specific orders
to restrict your access.

50:28.068 --> 50:29.635
Well, I'm overriding
those orders.

50:29.678 --> 50:31.593
And you are?

50:31.637 --> 50:33.117
The district attorney
in charge

50:33.160 --> 50:36.076
of reducing your career to
rubble should you piss me off.

50:36.120 --> 50:38.513
I'm Antonio Montez.

50:38.557 --> 50:40.037
I'm here to interview
the suspect.

50:40.080 --> 50:41.429
Yes, sir.

50:45.129 --> 50:46.695
I might have more luck
on my own.

50:48.175 --> 50:49.785
All right, go for it.

50:49.829 --> 50:52.049
[ Monitors beeping ]

50:54.399 --> 51:01.014
♪♪

51:01.058 --> 51:03.016
Hodges: Hear me in there?

51:03.060 --> 51:09.457
♪♪

51:09.501 --> 51:16.116
♪♪

51:16.160 --> 51:18.292
Olly olly oxen free.

51:20.468 --> 51:22.122
